        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 7:51AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 750 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Payne, or 12 miles northwest of Van Wert, moving northeast at 75 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Worstville, Ney, Jewell, Paulding, Arthur, Charloe, Payne, Tipton,
Ayersville, The Bend, Mcgill, Haviland, Brunersburg, Latty, Defiance,
Convoy, Briceton, Mark Center, Cecil, and Broughton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
